# AI Agent Instructions - Critical Rules

## 🚨 **READ FIRST**: Complete Documentation

**→ `docs/agents/system.md`** - Complete AI agent instructions (single source of truth)

## 🚨 **CRITICAL: NEVER Use `write` for Artifacts**

**FORBIDDEN:** `write` tool for files in `artifacts/` or `docs/bug_reports/`

**REQUIRED:** Use AgentQMS toolbelt

**Why:** Manual creation bypasses validation and violates project rules

```python
from agent_qms.toolbelt import check_before_write

# This will raise ManualCreationError if path is in artifacts/
check_before_write("artifacts/my-file.md")  # ❌ Raises error
```

## ✅ **Preferred: AgentQMS Toolbelt**

```python
from agent_qms.toolbelt import AgentQMSToolbelt

toolbelt = AgentQMSToolbelt()
artifact_path = toolbelt.create_artifact(
    artifact_type="assessment",  # or "implementation_plan", "bug_report"
    title="My Artifact",
    content="## Summary\n...",
    tags=["tag1", "tag2"]
)
```

**Available Types:** `assessment`, `implementation_plan`, `bug_report`

**Bug Reports:** Generate ID first: `uv run python scripts/bug_tools/next_bug_id.py`

## 📋 **Essential Rules**

**Naming:**
- Use lowercase with hyphens (kebab-case)
- No spaces, no ALL CAPS (except README.md, CHANGELOG.md)
- Timestamped for assessments/plans: `YYYY-MM-DD_HHMM_name.md`

**Frontmatter:** Required (title, timestamp, branch, status, tags)

**Progress Trackers:** Required for implementation plans and iterative assessments

